---
title: Strip Steak Bearnaise with Creamed Kale and Rosemary Potatoes
description: Béarnaise is one of the most elegant toppings you can put on a steak—the French sauce sings with fragrant tarragon and a splash of white wine vinegar. We’ve adapted it slightly to make it lighter and brighter, so that it bathes this New York strip in flavors that feel vibrant without being heavy. With creamed kale and crispy roasted spuds on the side, it feels like a luxuriant upgrade to classic meat and potatoes.
